Annotation.note:
A problem posed at International Mathematical Olympiad:
The triangle $OAB$ has angle $O$ acute. $M$ is an arbitary point on $AB$. $P$ and $Q$ are the feet of the perpendiculars from $M$ to $OA$ and $OB$ respectively. What is the locus of $H$, the orthocenter of the triangle $OPQ$ (the point where its altitudes meet)? What is the locus if $M$ is allowed to vary of the interior of $OAB$?
\begin{keywords} geometry theorem proving \end{keywords}
